  "title": "Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Site Supervision: </strong>Oversee daily construction activities ,ensure works are executed in line with approved drawings, method statements, and project specifications.</li></ul><ul><li><strong>Planning & Coordination: </strong>Coordinate with subcontractors,suppliers, and consultants to ensure timely progress of works.Monitor resources (manpower, equipment, and materials) to achieve planned targets.</li></ul><ul><li><strong>Quality Control & Documentation: </strong>Conduct site inspections and ensure compliance with project quality\nrequirements.Prepare and maintain daily site reports, inspection requests,material approvals, and as-built documentation.Support testing and commissioning activities.</li></ul><ul><li><strong>Health,Safety & Environment (HSE): </strong>Ensure compliance with all safety regulations and project-specific HSE\nrequirements.Conduct toolbox talks and promotes a safety-first culture at the site.</li></ul><ul><li><strong>Technical Support: </strong>Assist in resolving technical issues on-site in coordination with the engineering/design team.Review and interpret construction drawings, technical specifications, and standards.</li></ul><p><strong>Qualifications & Experience:</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s Degree/Diploma in Engineering,or related discipline.</li></ul><ul><li>3 years of site experience. </li></ul><ul><li>Proficient in MS Office, AutoCAD, and project management tools.</li></ul><ul><li>Strong problem-solving, leadershipand communication skills.</li></ul><ul></ul>",
